headline: Why Molina Healthcare (MOH) Stock Is Falling Today
summary: Shares of healthcare insurance company Molina Healthcare (NYSE:MOH) fell 10.6% in the pre-market session after the company reported underwhelming fourth quarter results, with EPS missing Wall Street estimates and full-year EPS guidance falling significantly short. However, full-year revenue guidance slightly exceeded analysts' expectations, and revenue outperformed estimates. Overall, the results were mixed.
